						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the Kuraṅganātha temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 37: 944-45 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the reign of Madiraikoṇḍa Parakēsarivarmaṉ.</p>						

						<p>It records a grant of 12 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> for a perpetual lamp, one <hi rend="italic">nilaiviḷakku</hi>, a copper pitcher for the occasion of the eclipse and one silver platter for <hi rend="italic">aḍaikkāy-amudu</hi> to god Paramēśvara of Tirukkurakkuttuṟai in Mahēndramaṅgalam by Pāgaṉ Śaṟpadēvaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śembiyaṉ Kiḻā[r]nāṭṭukōṉ of Kiḻinallūr in Kiḻā[r*]kūṟṟam.</p>						

						</summary>
